Questions:
Which of the following is considered an experimental procedure in the REBECCA-INCLIVA-Inter-QoL study?
A) Standard treatment with chemotherapy or radiotherapy;
B) Supportive telephone consultations providing general advice on recommended lifestyle habits;
C) Use of the REBECCA system to collect real-world data through mobile devices and apps;
D) Routine medical visits and standard clinical practice.

Correct answer: C

Who will have restricted access to your personally identified information according to the REBECCA study consent form?
A) Only the principal investigator and the study team;
B) Competent authorities, the Research Ethics Committee, and authorized sponsor personnel for data verification purposes;
C) All hospital staff members;
D) Any third-party advertisers for marketing purposes.

Correct answer: B
